<section class="page-header">
  <p class="eyebrow">Project story</p>
  <h1>About Move Your Way</h1>
  <p>
    Move Your Way is a data-driven wellness application inspired by Forever Living’s
    focus on movement, consistency and lifestyle-based wellness.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="content-grid">
  <div class="card">
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>
      Users land on the dashboard, view their progress, add an activity through a
      form and return to an updated dashboard with new data. They can also visit
      the history page to review previous movement entries.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>User Flow</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>User opens the dashboard.</li>
      <li>User reviews total minutes, activity count and streak.</li>
      <li>User clicks “Add Activity.”</li>
      <li>User submits the form.</li>
      <li>Dashboard updates with new data.</li>
      <li>User views past entries on the history page.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Design Rationale</h2>
    <p>
      The design uses green, cream and soft neutral colors to connect to wellness,
      aloe-inspired branding and a calm user experience. The layout is simple so
      users can focus on progress instead of pressure.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Wireframe Explanation</h2>
    <p>
      The dashboard includes a hero section, three progress cards, one chart and
      recent entries. The add activity page uses one clear form. The history page
      organizes saved activity data in a table.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>